citeinfo.title: Facilities Database

descript.abstract: The data is also complemented with the NYC Facilities Explorer, a new interactive web map that enables users to easily filter the data for their needs. Please visit the documentation sitefor more information. Important Note to Users: FacDB is only as good as the source data it aggregates, and the Department of City Planning cannot verify the accuracy of all records. Please read more about specific data and analysis limitations before using this data. Limitations include missing records, duplicate records, and the inclusion of administrative sites instead of service locations.
descript.purpose: The City Planning Facilities Database (FacDB) aggregates information about 35,000+ public and private facilities and program sites that are owned, operated, funded, licensed or certified by a City, State, or Federal agency in the City of New York. It captures facilities that generally help to shape quality of life in the city’s neighborhoods and are used for planning analyses related to siting new facilities and understanding the distribution of programs and services.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Feature geometry.
Universal Unique Identifier. When a row is added to the table the uid is automatically generated, enabling database replication.
Non-unique identifier generated and maintained by the former database admin that relates to old version of SFPSD.
Non-unique identifier generated and maintained by the data admin of the parent agency that relates to the record in the source dataset.
The name of the facility in proper case.

The address number of where the facility is located, validated by GeoClient. If the address that is available for the site is not complete with an address number (only the street name), this field is left blank.

The name of the street where the facility is located, validated by GeoClient. If the address that is available for the site is not complete with an address number (only the street name), this field is left blank.

The concatenated value of AddressNumber and StreetName of where the facility is located. If there is not a valid, complete address available, any location description that was provided is included in this field.

The USPS preferred name of the addressed city where the facility is located. Generated by GeoClient and spatial joins. This field contains some blanks for facilities that do not overlap with the shoreline Zip Code boundaries.
The full name the borough the facility is within.
The number value representing the borough the facility is within.
The ZIP Code the facility is within. This field contains some blanks for facilities that do not overlap with the shoreline Zip Code boundaries.
The latitude of the location either calculated using the coordinates in the source data or provided by GeoClient.
The longitude of the location either calculated using the coordinates in the source data or provided by GeoClient.
The X coordinate of the location either calculated using the coordinates in the source data or provided by GeoClient.
The Y coordinate of the location either calculated using the coordinates in the source data or provided by GeoClient.

The BIN values for the buildings the facility is located in. This field contains blanks, because 1) some lots do not have buildings on them, and 2) some lots have multiple buildings and a single BIN could not be reliably assigned given the information provided in the source data. There may also be cases where a facility is actually comprised by multiple BINs but only one is recorded in FacDB because the others were not be provided in the source data and could not be reliably assumed based on the single address provided for the facility.

The BBL values for the tax lots the facility is located on. This field contains blanks, because some facility categories, like pedestrian plazas are not located on tax lots. There may also be cases where a facility is actually comprised by multiple BBLs but only one is recorded in FacDB because the others were not be provided in the source data and could not be reliably assumed based on the single address provided for the facility.
The Community District the facility is within. This field contains blanks because the Community District boundaries do not capture facilities beyond the shoreline.
The City Council District the facility is within
The U.S. Census Tract the facility is within
The Neighborhood Tabulation Area (NTA) the facility is within. This field contains blanks because the NTA boundaries do not capture facilities beyond the shoreline.
The value representing the facility domain, the broadest category.
The value representing the group type, the second broadest category.
The value representing the subgroup type.
The value representing the facility type, the most granular category of facilities.

How many of capacity type/unit the facility is intended to hold. For many types of facilities, no capacity information was available. The capacity-related fields are blank when no information was provided in the source data.
The value representing the unit type of capacity, such as beds, visitors, seats, etc.
How many of capacity type/unit are being utilized at the facility.
The ratio of the of utilization over the total facility capacity.

The total area of the site measured in the Area Type unit. For many types of facilities, no area information was available. The area-related fields are blank when no information was provided in the source data.
The unit of measurement for Area.
Indicates whether the property is owned or leased by the City.
Indicates whether the operating entity is public or non-public.
The name of the operating entity.
Abbreviation for the operating entity.
The name of the agency overseeing the facility.
Abbreviation for the oversight agency.
The level of government of the oversight agency: City, State, City-State, Federal, or Non-public Oversight.
The date the source data was updated within the parent database.
The Agency whose data was used as the source for the record.
The name of the dataset the record came from.
Link to view and/or description of data.
